label: Front Slobode
title: Front_Slobode
exrest: Front Slobode was a newspaper that was launched in the middle of the World War II, on 7 November 1943 in Yugoslavia. It was of a regional character, published and distributed in North Eastern part of Bosnia and Herzegovina, and grew into a local Tuzla newspaper. It was a newspaper where Dervis Susic published a first story, and artist Ismet Mujezinovic created the masthead. The newspaper was changed from city ownership to private and finally, stopped operating as a newspaper in 2007.
